to the editor the proposal by gov gray davis of california to exempt teachers from the state income tax in an effort to increase teacher recruitment front page may 14 is misguided if teachers receive an income tax exemption what is to prevent public health nurses from demanding the same or other state workers or anyone else the proposal runs the risk of creating a two tiered structure of those who pay taxes and those who do n't that would hinder the state 's ability to cover its budget and fosters resentment between the professions lure the teachers with other benefits but keep their tax bill the same elizabeth marquardt waterville me may 15 2000

